# Chat Reading Skill — chat / WhatsApp → Packing List

How to read a chat conversation (WhatsApp export or free-text the user pastes)
and pull shipment facts into Packing List fields. Chat is fragmentary,
multi-party, and mixes Bahasa Indonesia with shipping jargon — collect facts
across many lines, then confirm with the user before creating a draft.

## Chat format
- WhatsApp export line: `[D/M/YY, H:MM:SS AM/PM] Sender: message`.
- Attachments appear as `<attached: filename.pdf>` — the file content is NOT in
  the text. Note the filename (it hints the doc type) and, if the data you need
  is only inside it, ask the user to send that document.
- System lines ("created group", "added you", "Messages and calls are
  end-to-end encrypted") carry no shipment data — skip them.

## What to extract (chat phrase → Packing List field)
| Said in chat | Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| "ETA Balikpapan KKT tgl 6Jun26 PM" | `eta` + `destination_location` | KKT = Kariangau terminal |
| "Feeder dari Tarakan" / leg Tarakan→Balikpapan | `origin_location` / `destination_location` | feeder leg |
| "MV Fu Haisheng … bawa cargo … ke Tarakan" | `vessel` (mother vessel) | |
| "TB RIAN UTAMA yg angkut lanjut" | feeder tug/barge → `vehicle` or note | not the mother vessel |
| "116 x 20ft TK" | `no_cargo`; `container_size` → "Container Size" | TK = tank |
| B/L / SWB numbers (ONL2605004) | `bl_no` | |
| Consignee codes (KRN / WPS / EUP) | item `customer` → resolve_master "CRM Organization" | KRN ≈ Kutai Refinery Nusantara |
| Shipping line / principal (ONT Shipping, KUKDONG) | `expedition` → resolve_master "Expedition" | |

## Indonesian shorthand glossary
- `tgl` = tanggal (date); `Jun26` / `6Jun26` = 6 June 2026; `PM` = sore/afternoon.
- `TK` = tank (isotank); `feeder` = feeder vessel; `kapal dr mana` = vessel origin.
- `muatan` = cargo; `SPB` = port clearance; `Exl manifes` = Excel manifest;
  `tercopy` = received/copied.

## Rules
- Chat rarely gives a clean B/L number, container list, or seals — those usually
  live in the attached documents. Use chat to capture vessel, voyage, route, ETA,
  quantity, and parties; then ask for the B/L/SWB to fill containers + seals.
- Multi-party threads contradict and correct each other — prefer the latest,
  most specific statement and confirm with the user.
- Resolve every Link via resolve_master. If a master is missing/ambiguous, show
  the candidates and ask — never guess.
- When the user just types a free-text description (not a WhatsApp export), treat
  the whole message as the shipment brief and apply the same field map.
